Scotland's independent schools have a ride performance of academic excellence, and it was continued in 2018 with another set of excellent exam results, which has only been reinforced by individual and collective successes in sports, art, music and other community enterprises.
With over 30,000 students across Scotland, these schools, represented by the Scottish Council for Independent Schools (SCIS), strive to provide the best level of service to their students and parents.
Independent schools aim to prepare their students for further and higher education, their chosen career, and their position as world citizens.
As an education sector that can design and implement a custom school curriculum, we see that world languages continue as a popular and desirable choice in schools.
Nelson Mandela said: \"If you talk to someone in a language he understands, it goes to his head.
